ssh

```
cd ~/.ssh
```
id_rsaid_rsa.pub
```
ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "youremail@example.com"
```

##
###
.ssh

```
cd ~/.ssh
vim id_rsa.pub
```
id_rsa.pub
.ssh ---> mkdir .ssh
authorized_keys ---> touch authorized_keys
   
###
1. ssh ~/.ssh/config

```
Host ssh_name()
HostName hostname(IP)IP
User user()
Port 22
IdentityFile pem_file_name
UseKeychain yes
...

```

2. , 

```shell
# ssh-add -K pem_file_name<enter>
# Enter passphrase for pem_file_name: password
```
       sudo chmod 0600 /Users/star/code/config/furuixing.pem
3. ok, `ssh ssh_name`
